ASSEMBLY JOINT RESOLUTION—Urging the Federal
Government to maintain the moratorium on the testing of
explosive nuclear weapons.
1 WHEREAS, The State of Nevada and its citizens have long
2 contributed to the national security of the United States by hosting
3 the Nevada National Security Site, formerly the Nevada Test Site,
4 where a total of 100 atmospheric tests and 828 underground tests
5 were conducted; and
6 WHEREAS, After sustained advocacy by Nevadans, the era of
7 explosive nuclear testing in the United States ended in 1992 when a
8 moratorium on underground nuclear testing was passed by
9 bipartisan majorities in the United States Congress and signed into
10 law by President George H.W. Bush, and the moratorium has been
11 voluntarily upheld by every president for over 30 years; and
12 WHEREAS, Former national security officials and other
13 Washington-based research organizations have recently called for
14 renewed explosive nuclear testing which, if adopted, would occur
15 underground at the Nevada National Security Site in Nye County,
16 just 65 miles from Las Vegas, Nevada, and would introduce
17 environmental, health and economic risks to all Nevadans; and
18 WHEREAS, When the Federal Government first selected the
19 Nevada Test Site for nuclear testing, an estimated 57,000 people
