1 and China, are signatories to the 1996 Comprehensive Nuclear Test
2 Ban Treaty; and
3 WHEREAS, Resumption of the testing of explosive nuclear
4 weapons would undermine the national security of the United States
5 by encouraging Russia, China and other countries to resume the
6 testing of nuclear weapons and improve their nuclear arsenals; and
7 WHEREAS, The United States has extensive data from having
8 conducted more nuclear tests than any other country, which fuels
9 today’s powerful science-based stockpile stewardship program with
10 cutting edge diagnostic, modeling and computing capabilities that
11 are second to none; and
12 WHEREAS, Polling conducted by the University of Maryland in
13 2024 found that more than two-thirds of Nevada Republicans and
14 Democrats favor continuing to abide by the moratorium on nuclear
15 testing; now, therefore, be it
16 RESOLVED BY THE ASSEMBLY AND SENATE OF THE STATE OF
17 NEVADA, JOINTLY, That the members of the 83rd Session of the
18 Nevada Legislature hereby urge the Federal Government to
19 maintain the moratorium on the testing of explosive nuclear
20 weapons; and be it further
21 RESOLVED, That the Chief Clerk of the Assembly prepare and
22 transmit a copy of this resolution to the President of the United
23 States, the Vice President of the United States as the presiding
24 officer of the Senate, the Speaker of the House of Representatives,
25 the United States Secretary of State, the United States Secretary of
26 Defense, the United States Secretary of Energy, the Under Secretary
27 for the National Nuclear Security Administration and each member
28 of the Nevada Congressional Delegation; and be it further
29 RESOLVED, That this resolution becomes effective upon
30 passage.
